Hello,
I am trying o make Cython 0.29.x  work with Python 3.12.0a5+, so @hrnciar can continue testing Fedora packages with pre-releases of Python 3.12.

The idea is that once I make it work I'll contribute backports here and/or other interested folks contribute backports here and I'll test them in Fedora.

*Note:* We have considered upgrading to Cython 3.0.0b1 but far too many of our packages are not buildable with it (I've asked @hrnciar to provide a summary of the failures to you, in case you'd like that).

Following up on https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/5238#issuecomment-1431349376 and https://github.com/cython/cython/commit/58d5fed61c I came up with this WIP patch for 0.29.33:

```patch
diff --git a/Cython/Utility/ModuleSetupCode.c b/Cython/Utility/ModuleSetupCode.c
index 33aac2c4a..b3de5dd75 100644
--- a/Cython/Utility/ModuleSetupCode.c
+++ b/Cython/Utility/ModuleSetupCode.c
@@ -210,6 +210,10 @@
   #elif !defined(CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS)
     #define CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS 1
   #endif
+  #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030C00A5
+    #undef CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS
+    #define CYTHON_USE_PYLONG_INTERNALS 0
+  #endif
   #ifndef CYTHON_USE_PYLIST_INTERNALS
     #define CYTHON_USE_PYLIST_INTERNALS 1
   #endif
@@ -252,7 +256,7 @@
     #define CYTHON_USE_TP_FINALIZE (PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030400a1)
   #endif
   #ifndef CYTHON_USE_DICT_VERSIONS
-    #define CYTHON_USE_DICT_VERSIONS (PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030600B1)
+    #define CYTHON_USE_DICT_VERSIONS ((PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030600B1) && (PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x030C00A5))
   #endif
   #if PY_VERSION_HEX >= 0x030B00A4
     #undef CYTHON_USE_EXC_INFO_STACK
```

EDIT: The patch above landed in 3397705da036bb2df4a5b8b4bf08dbad7bdb409f

This makes Cython at least build itself. However, the tests still fail.

Full logs: [builder-live.log.gz](https://github.com/cython/cython/files/10863603/builder-live.log.gz)

The test failures I could recognize are:

comment_data.body: I'm now building 3.0.0b1 again to see what test failures from above (if any) are missing.

> I am trying o make Cython 0.29.x work with Python 3.12.0a5+,

Cython 0.29.x will need some work in order to work with 3.12 release because there will be several removals breaking cython 0.29.X:
* `imp` module is going to be removed in 3.12 [1]. Cython 3 is not using `imp` module in latest versions of python but 0.29.X does. 
* `distutils` package  is going to be removed in 3.12 [2]. Cython 3 still depends on distutils but removal is planned in Cython 3.1 - see https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4405.
* There can be other functions used that are removed in 3.12 - https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/5134 but not sure, I have not investigated in deep.


[1] https://docs.python.org/3.11/library/imp.html
[2] https://docs.python.org/3/library/distutils.html

## builtins.bool size changed

Possibly https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/101394

```pycon
>>> bool.__basicsize__  # Python 3.12.0a4
32

>>> bool.__basicsize__  # Python 3.12.0a5
24
```

I might need to backport https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4894 which builds on top of https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4869

Draft PR: https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5289

>   * `distutils` package  is going to be removed in 3.12

That removal already happened and using distutils shipped via setuptools seems to work, at least for Fedora.

PyUnicode_FromUnicode still appears to be used in master, not sure why I didn't get the errors when I built b1:

https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/94bea667714567b9091aa25f2ca200c7b4e4f04c/Cython/Utility/TypeConversion.c#L99-L101

In order to support python 3.12 in Cython 0.29.X we need to backport following PRs (imp module is going to be removed -  https://github.com/python/cpython/pull/98573):

https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4941
https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4625

I can create backport PRs to 0.29.X branch.

>PyUnicode_FromUnicode still appears to be used in master

It's only used if you use the old Py_UNICODE type explicitly in your code. We disable the respective tests on CPython versions that no longer support it (without deprecation warnings).

> #4941

This looks small enough for a backport.

> #4625

This seems stretching it. I'd rather not risk issues with Py<3.12 in 0.29.x any more. I can live with pyximport being broken in Py3.12 and later in 0.29.x, it's really only a dev tool, not meant for production systems.

> I can live with pyximport being broken in Py3.12 and later in 0.29.x, it's really only a dev tool, not meant for production systems.

If we get too many issues, we could possibly split off a `pyximport_future` package so that people have something to use with Py3.12 and Cy 0.29.x. I'd be tempted not to do that until actually needed, but it's an option.

> PyUnicode_FromUnicode still appears to be used in master
> It's only used if you use the old Py_UNICODE type explicitly in your code. We disable the respective tests on CPython versions that no longer support it (without deprecation warnings).

9d38bf8d620fd09166a5469c76b54f66d7fbd828 / https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/5154

I disabled the usage of PyLong internals and dict versioning for Py3.12 in https://github.com/cython/cython/commit/3397705da036bb2df4a5b8b4bf08dbad7bdb409f, only for the 0.29.x branch, similar to your WIP patch above. Both are optimisations, it's ok to disable them for 0.29.x. Users who want fast support for Py3.12 should migrate to Cython 3.0.

I picked the change from https://github.com/cython/cython/commit/9d38bf8d620fd09166a5469c76b54f66d7fbd828 to disable the `py_unicode_strings` test and also worked around the exception output changes.
